---
description: Backend (NestJS) and web (Next.js) conventions
globs:
  - "backend/**/*.ts"
  - "web/**/*.ts"
  - "web/**/*.tsx"
alwaysApply: false
---

# App conventions

- Backend: NestJS modules/controllers/services; one module per feature. Validate request bodies with shared zod schemas before use. Port comes from `parseEnv().BACKEND_PORT`.
- Web: Next.js app router, server components by default, `"use client"` only when interactivity requires it. Backend base URL comes from `NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL` (default `http://localhost:4000`).
- Import shared code from `@mercato/shared` (the built package) — never deep-import `shared/src/*` files by relative path.
- After changing `shared/`, run `pnpm --filter @mercato/shared build` so backend and web pick up the new dist.
